It is hoped that the stage directions, which have been mainly suggested by practical experience at Westminster, may be of real service.

Constant use has been made of the editions of Umpfenbach‚ Fleckeisen, Dziatzko, Wagner, Bond and Walpole,-—the first two on textual questions only‚—with less frequent reference to those of Bentley, Zeune (containing the commentaries of Donatus), Stallbaum, Parry, and Davies. References are made to Roby’s School Latin Grammar as more likely to be generally accessible than his larger work.
